com.k2.Util.exceptions

Class FileLockedException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • com.k2.Util.exceptions.FileLockedException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class FileLockedException
extends java.lang.Exception
    This exception is thrown when a file has been locked using java's FileLock API and an application attempts to lock the file.
    Author:
    simon
